The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the number of distinct distances from a vertex of a convex polygon. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves combinatorial and discrete mathematics, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), and graph theory (cs.GT), which are all relevant to the problem at hand.
